ent highs and the desk carrying a bearish read into the session.\n\nThe structure story begins with the recovery leg that carried EUR/USD from the 1.1324 area in late June up to a session high of 1.14818 on 15 July \u2014 a move of roughly 160 pips that represented the clearest directional impulse in the observed window. Since that peak, however, the daily candles have been progressively lower-closing: 1.14633, 1.14431, 1.14377, 1.14387, 1.14316, 1.14146, 1.13979, and now 1.14066. That sequence of declining closes from a swing high is the core of the bearish read. The prior reaction zone at 1.14429 has been tested on multiple occasions and has demonstrably capped intraday advances, with the 15 July high representing the only meaningful breach \u2014 one that was swiftly rejected. The 1.14827 zone sits as the next structural resistance above that, having attracted sellers on three prior occasions. These levels are not arbitrary; they represent areas where supply has historically overwhelmed demand.\n\nOn the H1 chart, the picture is one of orderly drift lower. From the 1.14290 area seen during yesterday's European hours, price has ground steadily down through the Asian session and into the London open, finding a tentative floor in the 1.13976\u20131.14000 zone. The morning's price action has been tight \u2014 roughly a 10-pip range across several hours \u2014 suggesting the market is in a wait-and-see posture. There is no meaningful intraday momentum in either direction, though the sequence of lower H1 closes from yesterday afternoon onwards is consistent with the broader bearish lean. The 1.14098 area, which capped the overnight bounce, now functions as a near-term intraday reference.\n\nToday's calendar is light, with only the US Crude Oil Inventories release at 10:30 UTC flagged, and that carries a low impact designation for EUR/USD specifically. The absence of high-impact event risk means the pair is unlikely to receive an external catalyst to break it out of the current consolidation. That said, thin catalysts can occasionally amplify moves in already-trending markets, so the afternoon session warrants attention if the 1.13980 intraday support gives way.\n\nThe bearish read would require reassessment on a sustained H4 close back above the 1.14429 prior reaction zone. A recapture of that level on volume would suggest the pullback from the July high is complete rather than developing, and would shift the near-term picture back toward neutral. Until that occurs, the structure of declining daily closes from the 1.14818 swing high remains the dominant narrative.\n\nThis is editorial analysis, not financial advice. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.", "sample": false}